sailpoint.api.nativeidentitychange

Interface NativeIdentityChangePropagator

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractNativeIdentityChangePropagator, AbstractNativeIdentityChangeRolePropagator, AccountNativeIdentityChangeIdentityPropagator, GroupNativeIdentityChangeIdentityPropagator, NativeIdentityChangeApplicationPropagator, NativeIdentityChangeCorrelationConfigPropagator, NativeIdentityChangeDynamicScopePropagator, NativeIdentityChangeFormPropagator, NativeIdentityChangeGenericPropagator, NativeIdentityChangeGroupDefinitionPropagator, NativeIdentityChangeIdentityTriggerPropagator, NativeIdentityChangePasswordPolicyHolderPropagator, NativeIdentityChangePolicyPropagator, NativeIdentityChangeRolePropagatorCorrelationModel, NativeIdentityChangeRulePropagator

    public interface NativeIdentityChangePropagator
    Interface of NativeIdentityChangeEvent propagators. New implementations of this interface should not implement it directly but should extend AbstractNativeIdentityChangePropagator, which has reasonable default implementations for everything except NativeIdentityChangePropagator.processEvents(SailPointContext, List, TaskResult).

    The primary method here is processEvents(SailPointContext, List, TaskResult). This method is responsible for processing a list of NativeIdentityChangeEvents and updating the TaskResult accordingly. The other methods are largely used for bookkeeping purposes to keep track of which objects have already been processed so that they can be skipped if the request needs to be retried.

    processEvents implementations are responsible for handling all necessary locks/commits/rollbacks.

    Implementing classes may call NativeIdentityChangePropagator.hasObjectProcessed(Class, String) and/or NativeIdentityChangePropagator.haveAllObjectsProcessed(Class) to avoid repeating propagation to already-processed objects on retry. Implementing classes MUST call NativeIdentityChangePropagator.markObjectProcessed(Class, String) each time an object has been processed and committed for every event, and MUST call NativeIdentityChangePropagator.markAllObjectsProcessed(Class) upon completion of the entire list of objects for every event.

    • Method Detail

      • processEvents

        boolean processEvents(SailPointContext context,
                      java.util.List<NativeIdentityChangeEvent> changeEvents,
                      TaskResult taskResult)
               throws GeneralException
        Processes the list of NativeIdentityChangeEvents. Typically this entails renaming every instance of old native identity strings (NativeIdentityChangeEvent.getOldNativeIdentity()) to new native identity strings (NativeIdentityChangeEvent.getNewNativeIdentity()) in a set of objects of interest, although custom subclasses can do pretty much anything.

        Implementations will have to supply this method.

        Parameters:
        context - The SailPointContext
        changeEvents - The list of NativeIdentityChangeEvents to process
        taskResult - The TaskResult
        Returns:
        true If the entire list of events was processed successfully
        Throws:
        GeneralException - is treated by NativeIdentityChangePropagationRequestExecutor as if it were a permanent exception.
        sailpoint.request.RequestTemporaryException - for conditions where it is known to be possible to retry the request.
        sailpoint.request.RequestPermanentException - for conditions where it is known that a retry would not lead to a better outcome.

      • terminateRequestOnError
